In a speech at the Rose Garden, Vice President Kamala Harris and President Joe Biden addressed the celebration of Asian American, Native Hawaiian, and Pacific Islander Heritage Month. They acknowledged the contributions of Asian Americans to the country and emphasized the importance of treating all people with dignity and respect. They also condemned hate crimes and discrimination and highlighted the need to end the epidemic of hate. President Biden mentioned the signing of the COVID-19 Hate Crimes Act and reiterated his commitment to advancing equality for all Americans. He also honored the late Norman Mineta, an Asian American leader and former Cabinet Secretary, and emphasized the importance of diversity and unity in America.